ndency; Hibernate Validator 9.x documentation recommends an EL 6 implementation instead.\",\n    \"The reporter reproduced through Spring Boot, whose validation starter supplies Tomcat's EL implementation, but direct Hibernate Validator bootstrap should still reach the same validator/logger initialization path without adding Spring Boot.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05f16cac7ca27e29016a3bf10eb4388196b709ccde159dc02b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1838, "output": 820, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25186, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782313221463, "responseId": "resp_05f16cac7ca27e29016a3bf1060dbc819681d6f78b51a5497a"}, "toolResults": []}
